      "fix": "Replace the naïve O(2^n * n * m) loops with a faster evaluation of the weight vector using bitmask pre‑computation. Represent each column j as an n‑bit integer colMask[j] where bit i is 1 iff student i answered question j correctly. Then for a given mask (the sign vector encoded as a bitmask) the weight w_j = popcount(mask & colMask[j]) - popcount((~mask) & colMask[j]), which can be computed with a single popcount per column. This reduces the inner work to O(m) per mask with a very small constant factor, making the total runtime comfortably below the limit. Additionally, early exit when best possible value cannot be exceeded can be added, but the bitmask optimisation alone resolves the TLE.",
